TearsLibrary
Created by: Gabriel Sevilha

Project init: 06/15/2020
Project first release: 16/06/2020

TearsLibrary is a graphics library write in C/C++ to help write applications without worrying with a low level api, so you can dedicate for your project development accelerating you development

TearsLibrary References:

	Compile links:
	
		-lgdi32 -lgdiplus

	Classes:
	
		Display:
			Display(const char* title,int width,int height,bool fullscreen,bool vsync);
			void show();
			void shutdown();
		
		Image:
			Image(const char* file);
			draw();
			setPosition(int x, int y);
			setSize(int w, int h);

	Functions:
	
		void setColor(int r, int g, int b);
		void setPenSize(int size);
		void fillRect(int x, int y, int w, int h);
		void fillEllipse(int x, int y, int r);
		void drawPixel(int x, int y);
		void drawRect(int x, int y, int w, int h);
		void drawEllipse(int x, int y, int r);
		void drawLine(int x, int y, int final_x, int final_y);

Program exemple:

	Draw polygon:
	
		int point[] = {
			400,100,
			100,500,
			700,500
		};
		fillPolygon(point,3);
